1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,400
Hey, family, I'm excited to be with you again this week

2
00:00:03,400 --> 00:00:05,680
and to jump into the Word of God together

3
00:00:05,680 --> 00:00:07,360
and discover what God has for us

4
00:00:07,360 --> 00:00:09,360
and the truth that He has for us

5
00:00:09,360 --> 00:00:13,160
to encourage us in the places that we're in life right now

6
00:00:13,160 --> 00:00:15,200
and the things that we're going through

7
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:16,920
This week, we're actually going to step away

8
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:19,080
from the Sermon on the Mount for just a little bit

9
00:00:19,080 --> 00:00:21,360
and we're going to look at another kingdom value

10
00:00:21,360 --> 00:00:25,040
and that is the kingdom value of loving our neighbors

11
00:00:25,040 --> 00:00:26,720
And we're going to be looking at this today

12
00:00:26,720 --> 00:00:30,560
just because there's so much going on in our world right now

13
00:00:30,560 --> 00:00:34,040
And as believers, we want to respond to those things

14
00:00:34,040 --> 00:00:36,040
We want to love our neighbors well

15
00:00:36,040 --> 00:00:39,040
And Jesus has some really good advice for us

16
00:00:39,040 --> 00:00:41,600
in the scripture about how to do that

17
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:43,680
And it's almost overwhelming at times

18
00:00:43,680 --> 00:00:45,840
all the things that we see going on in our world

19
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:49,760
We have this coup that's going on in Myanmar

20
00:00:49,760 --> 00:00:52,280
where the military has taken control of the country

21
00:00:52,280 --> 00:00:53,760
and there's all types of violence

22
00:00:53,760 --> 00:00:55,960
and people being oppressed

23
00:00:55,960 --> 00:00:58,080
and voices that are being suppressed

24
00:00:58,080 --> 00:01:00,120
and people being hurt

25
00:01:00,120 --> 00:01:03,600
And there's this terrible situation in Hong Kong

26
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:05,600
where freedoms are being stolen away

27
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:08,640
and dissent is being stifled and silenced

28
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:12,400
And we have all types of religious violence in the world

29
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:14,680
We have places in the Middle East and Africa

30
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:17,120
where Christians are persecuted and assaulted

31
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:19,360
We have violence right here in the city of Chicago

32
00:01:19,360 --> 00:01:20,720
We have violence on our streets

33
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:26,000
where people are harmed and killed and shot every day

34
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,440
in the city of Chicago

35
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:31,080
And we have all these other problems in the United States

36
00:01:31,080 --> 00:01:34,520
We have all these issues with racism that we've seen

37
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:37,560
just be so out in the open over the last year

38
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:39,560
And even in the last week, we see this incident

39
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:44,080
that involves possible racism against Asian Americans

40
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:46,800
And so there's so much stuff happening

41
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:49,800
And it's hurtful and it's terrible

42
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:52,160
and it's discouraging to see

43
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:54,920
But Jesus wants us to respond to those things

44
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:58,280
as the people of God, as the subjects of the kingdom

45
00:01:58,280 --> 00:02:01,400
It's a kingdom value for us to love the people around us

46
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:03,320
and to love the world around us

47
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:05,120
And it can be difficult to know

48
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:07,320
and understand how we can do that

49
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:09,160
So that's what we're going to look at today

50
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:12,320
We're going to look at this story in Luke chapter 10

51
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:13,680
It's a really familiar story

52
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:15,640
It's the story of the Good Samaritan

53
00:02:15,640 --> 00:02:18,160
I think there's some good advice for us here

54
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:19,920
that Jesus himself gives us

55
00:02:19,920 --> 00:02:22,520
about how to love our neighbors

56
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:24,800
how to love those around us

57
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:26,320
So let's read this together

58
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:28,560
and then we're going to dig into it a little bit

59
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:30,160
We'll begin in verse 25

60
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:33,320
This is Luke chapter 10, verse 25

61
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:34,840
It says this

62
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:38,800
And behold, a lawyer stood up to him

63
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,320
to put him to the test, saying,

64
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:43,960
Teacher, what shall I do to inherit eternal life?

65
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:46,680
He said to him, what is written in the law?

66
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:48,040
How do you read it?

67
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,680
And he answered, You shall love the Lord your God

68
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:50,960
with all your heart, with all your soul

69
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:52,760
with all your strength, with all your mind

70
00:02:52,760 --> 00:02:54,720
and your neighbor as yourself

71
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:56,720
And he said to him, You have answered correctly

72
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:58,800
Do this and you will live

73
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:01,280
But he desiring to justify himself

74
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:04,120
said to Jesus, And who is my neighbor?

75
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:07,480
Jesus replied, A man was going down

76
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:08,800
from Jerusalem to Jericho

77
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,080
and he fell among robbers

78
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,320
who stripped him and beat him

79
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:14,080
and departed, leaving him half dead

80
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:17,160
Now by chance, a priest was going down that road

81
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:20,160
and when he saw him, he passed by on the other side

82
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:23,360
So likewise a Levite, when he had come to the place

83
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:26,920
and saw him, passed by on the other side

84
00:03:26,920 --> 00:03:29,200
But a Samaritan, as he journeyed

85
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:30,880
came to where he was

86
00:03:30,880 --> 00:03:34,040
and when he saw him, he had compassion

87
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:36,680
He went to him and bound up his wounds

88
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:38,920
pouring on oil and wine

89
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:41,080
Then he set him on his own animal

90
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:44,320
and brought him to an inn and took care of him

91
00:03:44,320 --> 00:03:46,760
And the next day he took out two denarii

92
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:48,200
and gave them to the innkeeper

93
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:49,320
saying, Take care of him

94
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:51,080
and whatever more you spend

95
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:54,240
I will repay you when I come back

96
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:56,000
Which of these three do you think

97
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,720
proved to be a neighbor to the man

98
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:59,920
who fell among the robbers?

99
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:03,200
He said, The one who showed him mercy

100
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:08,000
And Jesus said to him, You go and do likewise

101
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,200
Now in this story, what's going on here is

102
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:12,000
there's this discussion taking place

103
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:15,440
and this lawyer, he's an expert in the Jewish law

104
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:18,160
comes to Jesus and in verse 25

105
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:20,480
tells us he's kind of trying to trip Jesus up

106
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:23,120
He wants to make Jesus look bad

107
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:25,920
and ask him a really tough question

108
00:04:25,920 --> 00:04:28,440
and he says, How do I inherit eternal life?

109
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:30,680
And so Jesus puts the question back on him

110
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:32,600
and says, Well, what does the law say?

111
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,280
How do you read it?

112
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:35,480
What's important that you see in the law?

113
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:37,720
And so this man says, Well, I think

114
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:39,920
the most important thing in the law

115
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:41,920
is to love God with all your mind

116
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,720
and your strength and your soul

117
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:45,400
and to love your neighbor as yourself

118
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:48,640
And so Jesus says, You've answered correctly

119
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:51,640
But this man doesn't want to leave it there

120
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:54,160
And I love this verse, verse number 29

121
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:57,360
where it says, He seeking to justify himself

122
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:58,800
desire to justify himself

123
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,560
He says to Jesus, Who is my neighbor?

124
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:01,600
It's such a great verse

125
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,200
because that's all of us as humans

126
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:05,680
We're always trying to justify ourselves

127
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,320
to make ourselves look good

128
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:08,680
in the sight of God and others

129
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:09,760
And that's what he's doing here

130
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:11,280
He's saying, Yeah, but Jesus

131
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:12,560
you've got to understand

132
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:15,720
like, I've already done this, you know

133
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:17,360
And if there's a problem here

134
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,520
it's not because I'm not doing it

135
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:20,080
It's maybe just because I don't understand

136
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:22,280
what it means, some of the words mean

137
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:23,520
So who is my neighbor?

138
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:25,680
Why don't you tell me who my neighbor is?

139
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:27,520
And then Jesus responds

140
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:29,320
with this amazing story

141
00:05:29,320 --> 00:05:31,120
He tells a story about a man

142
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:34,000
who is going from Jerusalem to Jericho

143
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,880
and he gets robbed, brutally beaten

144
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:40,080
And he's laying by the side of the road

145
00:05:40,080 --> 00:05:43,040
Bleeding, and his clothes are stolen

146
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:44,920
And he's left for dead

147
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:46,440
He's laying there dying

148
00:05:46,440 --> 00:05:48,200
by the side of the road

149
00:05:48,200 --> 00:05:50,360
And people begin to pass him by

150
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:51,880
The first person that Jesus tells us

151
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:53,680
that passes is a priest

152
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:56,000
He's coming down that same road

153
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:56,880
He sees this man

154
00:05:56,880 --> 00:06:00,400
He goes to the other side and passes by

155
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:01,800
And next comes a Levite

156
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:03,120
And he does the same thing

157
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:06,080
He sees this man and passes him by

158
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:07,480
on the other side

159
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:08,360
And then Jesus says

160
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:10,200
A Samaritan comes

161
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,920
And this is huge

162
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:14,680
This fact, the hero of this story

163
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:15,800
is a Samaritan

164
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:17,480
The Samaritan, the Jews

165
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:19,560
were people who did not like each other

166
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:21,040
at all for ethnic reasons

167
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:24,040
So there's so much about race and ethnicity

168
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:24,920
in this passage

169
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,880
That's a whole, could be a whole

170
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:28,000
series of messages

171
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,560
And that's not what we're looking at today

172
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:32,520
So I don't have time to unpack all that

173
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:34,400
But we need to unpack that in some way

174
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:35,320
Because this is huge

175
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:37,160
what Jesus is teaching here

176
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:39,600
by making the Samaritan the other

177
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:42,920
the person who was despised by the Jews

178
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:44,160
He's the hero of the story

179
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:45,800
He's the one who actually shows

180
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:47,040
the character of the kingdom

181
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:49,200
And he's actually obedient in a way

182
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:52,600
that the Jewish priest and Levite were not

183
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,320
But he's the one who comes along

184
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:56,200
and shows compassion

185
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:57,880
He goes to this person

186
00:06:57,880 --> 00:07:00,360
who's dying by the side of the road

187
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:01,760
He binds up his wounds

188
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:02,600
He takes care of him

189
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:04,040
He banishes him

190
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:05,920
He makes sure that he's okay

191
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,840
And then he puts him on his animal

192
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:08,600
on his donkey

193
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:09,920
that he was traveling with

194
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:11,120
Takes him to an inn

195
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:12,240
a place of lodging

196
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:14,200
where this person can be cared for

197
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:16,960
And make sure that he's cared for

198
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:18,000
And then in verse 35

199
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:20,560
we see that he even pays for it himself

200
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:22,400
And gives money to the innkeeper

201
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:23,480
and says take care of him

202
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:25,240
And when I come back

203
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:26,320
if there's anything else

204
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:27,720
that needs to be taken care of

205
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,480
I'll pay for all of it

206
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:31,720
And so he takes care of this stranger

207
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,480
in an amazing way

208
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:35,040
And Jesus closes the story

209
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:38,120
by asking who was the neighbor

210
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:40,040
And clearly it's a rhetorical question

211
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:42,400
The answer is the Samaritan

212
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:45,720
And we see this expert in the law

213
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:47,760
unable to even name the Samaritan

214
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:48,760
And just saying the one

215
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:50,600
who showed him mercy

216
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,520
But Jesus is showing us a lot here

217
00:07:52,520 --> 00:07:53,600
about who our neighbor is

218
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,480
And maybe you're familiar

219
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:55,080
with this story

220
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:57,680
Maybe you've heard it told before

221
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,880
And maybe you've heard people

222
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:00,400
kind of focus on the fact that

223
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:03,000
our neighbor could be anyone

224
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,360
And as I said in the context

225
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,280
of this story ethnically

226
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:06,720
It could certainly be the people

227
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:07,720
that are different from us

228
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:10,320
That maybe we don't want to love

229
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:11,680
or to care for

230
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:14,200
That's a huge part of this story

231
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:16,120
But what I want us to focus on today

232
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:18,320
Is how we're supposed to respond

233
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:19,960
to a neighbor

234
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:20,840
Whoever that is

235
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:22,200
Wherever that is

236
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,040
Who is suffering

237
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:24,920
Because we do see so much brokenness

238
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:26,760
And so much suffering in our world

239
00:08:26,760 --> 00:08:28,000
And as the people of God

240
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,160
We're supposed to respond

241
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:30,280
But how do we respond

242
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:32,120
How can we respond

243
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:33,640
And I think there's a lot of truth

244
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:35,560
In this story for us

245
00:08:35,560 --> 00:08:36,120
So the first thing

246
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,080
I want us to consider

247
00:08:37,080 --> 00:08:39,360
Is that we should

248
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:41,960
And we must allow God

249
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:44,520
To interrupt the rhythms of our lives

250
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:46,840
With the sufferings of others

251
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:47,840
Look at verse 33

252
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:49,680
It says but a Samaritan

253
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:51,120
As he journeyed

254
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:51,720
What's he doing

255
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:53,000
He's on this road

256
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,600
From Jerusalem to Jericho

257
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:55,400
We don't know why

258
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:56,240
It doesn't tell us that

259
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:57,000
We don't know if maybe

260
00:08:57,000 --> 00:09:00,080
He's journeying for business purposes

261
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:01,200
Maybe he's a merchant

262
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:03,560
He's going to one of those cities

263
00:09:03,560 --> 00:09:05,280
To sell something

264
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:06,920
Maybe he's journeying

265
00:09:06,920 --> 00:09:08,280
To meet family members

266
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:09,960
Maybe he's going to a wedding

267
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,600
Or a special occasion

268
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:12,920
We don't really know

269
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:14,680
Because the story doesn't tell us that

270
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:16,080
But he's journeying

271
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:17,680
As a part of the rhythm of his life

272
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:18,240
Obviously

273
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:20,240
No one just takes a long journey

274
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:21,760
And this was a long

275
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:24,080
And dangerous journey on this road

276
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:25,240
Because this road was known

277
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:27,040
To be frequented by bandits

278
00:09:27,040 --> 00:09:28,120
No one takes a long

279
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:30,000
And dangerous journey for no reason

280
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:30,720
There was something

281
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:31,880
In the rhythm of his life

282
00:09:31,880 --> 00:09:33,200
That he was doing

283
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:33,680
Like I said

284
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:35,080
Maybe it was for personal reasons

285
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:37,080
Maybe it was for business

286
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:38,000
Or work or something

287
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,320
But there was something

288
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:40,840
That he was doing

289
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:41,960
And that

290
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,600
Whatever that purpose was

291
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,160
It was interrupted

292
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:48,240
When he saw this suffering person

293
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:49,520
And let's contrast that

294
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:51,680
With the priest and Levi

295
00:09:51,680 --> 00:09:53,680
Who they are going about

296
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:55,240
The rhythm of their life

297
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:57,600
And they do not allow

298
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,560
The rhythm of their life

299
00:09:58,560 --> 00:09:59,680
To be interrupted

300
00:09:59,680 --> 00:10:01,720
By this suffering person

301
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:02,200
And again

302
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:03,600
This story doesn't tell us

303
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:05,400
Their reasoning necessarily

304
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:06,720
I'm sure there are a lot of reasons

305
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:07,560
But we can imagine

306
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:08,400
Maybe some of the things

307
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:09,920
They were thinking

308
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:12,040
Maybe for the priest especially

309
00:10:12,040 --> 00:10:13,400
Maybe it had to do with the fact

310
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:16,080
That he was ceremonially clean

311
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:17,720
And he wasn't supposed to touch

312
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:18,680
Things that were unclean

313
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:19,400
And maybe he was saying

314
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:21,440
Oh that person is bloody

315
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:23,040
And if I go over there

316
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:24,200
And get involved

317
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:25,480
It'll create a mess

318
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:27,280
And it might make me unclean

319
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:28,840
And then I'm not able to serve

320
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:29,880
In the way that I'm supposed to

321
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:31,080
In the temple

322
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:33,080
Isn't that ironic

323
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:35,560
That perhaps the priest

324
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:37,120
Was afraid of the mess

325
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,040
That would be involved

326
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:39,800
In getting involved

327
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:40,600
In the life of someone

328
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:41,560
Who's suffering

329
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:43,280
And that's what kept him

330
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:44,840
From actually doing the thing

331
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:47,640
That his faith called him to do

332
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:49,520
From loving his neighbor

333
00:10:49,520 --> 00:10:51,800
In the way that God wanted him to

334
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:52,880
What kept him from it

335
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:53,760
Was that he felt like

336
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:55,000
He was serving God

337
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,080
By remaining clean

338
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:58,920
Isn't that ironic to think about

339
00:10:58,920 --> 00:10:59,880
That he felt like

340
00:10:59,880 --> 00:11:02,520
Oh what I have to do

341
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:03,560
And the way I have to do it

342
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:05,080
Is so important

343
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:06,520
That I can't interrupt

344
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:08,200
The rhythm of my life

345
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,520
The Levi

346
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:11,280
He's a servant in the temple

347
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:12,440
And again we don't know exactly

348
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,480
What's going on in his head

349
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:15,240
But maybe he was like

350
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:16,520
Well I'm busy

351
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:17,840
I've got to get to the temple

352
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:19,280
To do this thing

353
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:20,840
Or I have this important role to play

354
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:23,320
Or I'm supposed to take care of something

355
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:24,960
And I just don't have time

356
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:28,560
Or maybe these other roles in my life

357
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:30,120
I feel like they're much more important

358
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:32,920
Than stopping to deal with this suffering person

359
00:11:32,920 --> 00:11:34,000
Or maybe they were afraid

360
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,200
Maybe they just felt like

361
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:35,760
Well I don't know

362
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:36,600
I've got to hurry

363
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,040
Because the bandits might come back

364
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:40,080
I mean clearly something terrible happened

365
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:41,360
And I just need to hurry

366
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:43,920
And get safe as quickly as I can

367
00:11:43,920 --> 00:11:46,640
Or maybe they were just uncomfortable

368
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:48,680
We don't really know why

369
00:11:48,680 --> 00:11:49,880
Or for whatever reason

370
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:51,240
The priest and the Levi

371
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:53,360
Didn't allow God to interrupt

372
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:54,440
The rhythms of their life

373
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:56,920
They didn't allow God

374
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:58,440
To interrupt them on their journey

375
00:11:58,440 --> 00:12:00,600
Whatever they were headed to

376
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:01,800
They didn't stop

377
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:03,800
And see this person who was suffering

378
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:07,080
And say I want to help

379
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:09,200
And as followers of Jesus

380
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,440
As a subject of the kingdom

381
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:12,040
We've got to learn

382
00:12:12,040 --> 00:12:14,680
To let God interrupt the rhythms of our life

383
00:12:14,680 --> 00:12:16,600
With the suffering of others

384
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,080
When we see someone

385
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:20,680
Across the street or across the world

386
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:22,080
Maybe it's in our neighborhood

387
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,400
Maybe it's right there

388
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:25,160
Maybe it's a news story

389
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:26,640
We see on the other side of the world

390
00:12:26,640 --> 00:12:28,320
Or maybe it's a friend or a family member

391
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,760
That we have in another place

392
00:12:29,760 --> 00:12:30,720
Across the world

393
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:33,400
Or even just across the city

394
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:35,160
Or in another state

395
00:12:35,160 --> 00:12:37,600
And we hear about suffering in our life

396
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:39,920
We need to allow those things

397
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:41,320
To interrupt the rhythm of our life

398
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:42,160
Don't just say you know what

399
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:42,680
I'm busy

400
00:12:42,680 --> 00:12:44,240
I've got more important stuff to do

401
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:45,680
And what I have to do

402
00:12:45,680 --> 00:12:46,920
Is really a big deal

403
00:12:46,920 --> 00:12:49,560
My job, my friendships, my relationships

404
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:51,800
I can't stop to help someone

405
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:53,480
We should allow God

406
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:56,000
To interrupt the rhythms of our life

407
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,520
And let's think about how God does that

408
00:12:57,520 --> 00:12:59,400
You know a lot of times God does that

409
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:01,400
With things that have proximity to us

410
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:05,040
Things that are close to us in some way

411
00:13:05,040 --> 00:13:07,480
And I think that's important for us to consider

412
00:13:07,480 --> 00:13:10,480
Obviously there's so much brokenness in the world

413
00:13:10,480 --> 00:13:11,960
And so much suffering in the world

414
00:13:11,960 --> 00:13:14,800
It's completely impossible for one person

415
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:16,880
Or even for one group of people

416
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:19,000
To wrap their minds around

417
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,160
All the suffering in the world

418
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:21,680
And to care about all of it

419
00:13:21,680 --> 00:13:22,680
And to pray about all of it

420
00:13:22,680 --> 00:13:24,320
And to help in all of it

421
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:27,200
There's no way one person could do that

422
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:29,040
And so I'm not saying that we have to try

423
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:32,120
To involve ourself in every problem in the world

424
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:33,560
And every time anything happens

425
00:13:33,560 --> 00:13:34,840
We have to take care of everything

426
00:13:34,840 --> 00:13:36,720
And every person who has a need

427
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:38,200
We have to meet that need

428
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:40,880
No, that would drive us crazy

429
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:42,360
And completely exhaust us

430
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:44,920
There's no way we can do that

431
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:46,320
But we do need to understand

432
00:13:46,320 --> 00:13:48,520
That the things that happen in our life

433
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:50,120
Happen for a reason

434
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:52,160
And so when God interrupts our rhythm

435
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:55,560
When he crosses our path with something

436
00:13:55,560 --> 00:13:57,760
That's because he does want us

437
00:13:57,760 --> 00:14:01,280
To have our life interrupted by it

438
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:03,280
And to respond to it

439
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:06,560
Again, we don't have to respond to everything

440
00:14:06,560 --> 00:14:09,600
But to the things that God brings into our life

441
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:12,280
We should be ready and willing to respond

442
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:15,360
And that's what we see here with the Samaritan

443
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:17,840
He wasn't out on the road

444
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:19,840
Trying to find people who are hurt

445
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:21,320
And help every person

446
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:23,600
That might have potentially been hurt on the road

447
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:24,560
He wasn't out on the road

448
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:25,840
Trying to find the bandits

449
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,960
And to stop them from robbing people

450
00:14:27,960 --> 00:14:31,400
He was just going about the rhythm of his life

451
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:34,520
But God brought this suffering person

452
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:35,640
Close to him

453
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:37,640
And he allowed that suffering

454
00:14:37,640 --> 00:14:39,560
To interrupt the rhythm of his life

455
00:14:39,560 --> 00:14:41,200
And when you find yourself

456
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,680
In a place of proximity

457
00:14:42,680 --> 00:14:44,600
To someone who is suffering

458
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:45,360
Then you should

459
00:14:45,360 --> 00:14:46,640
That should be a light bulb

460
00:14:46,640 --> 00:14:47,560
That goes off in your head

461
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:48,440
And you say, wait a second

462
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:50,680
Maybe God is allowing this to happen

463
00:14:50,680 --> 00:14:52,520
Because God wants me to get involved

464
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:55,160
In this situation or in this person's life

465
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:58,000
God wants me to respond in some way

466
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:59,440
I just want to remind us

467
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:00,400
That that proximity

468
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:03,400
Isn't only a geographical proximity

469
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:05,520
In this case, it was a geographical proximity

470
00:15:05,520 --> 00:15:07,440
The Samaritan was walking back past

471
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:09,520
And he saw this person suffering

472
00:15:09,520 --> 00:15:11,200
But it doesn't just have to be that

473
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:12,640
It could be relational

474
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:13,720
It could be someone

475
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:15,920
That maybe they're not close by you

476
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:17,480
In physical proximity

477
00:15:17,480 --> 00:15:18,760
But you have a relationship with them

478
00:15:18,760 --> 00:15:20,560
They're a friend or they're a family member

479
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:22,240
Or they're someone that you know

480
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:24,560
And you see them suffering in a way

481
00:15:24,560 --> 00:15:27,440
And you say, hey, I think

482
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:29,280
That God wants me to be involved

483
00:15:29,280 --> 00:15:30,200
And respond there

484
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:32,080
Because he's brought this suffering

485
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:32,600
Close to me

486
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:33,760
And he's brought it to my attention

487
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:34,960
And he's put it in front of me

488
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:37,160
And I have a role to play in this

489
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:40,200
It could be some other type of connection

490
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:41,760
It could be some type of affinity

491
00:15:41,760 --> 00:15:44,240
Something that you are interested in

492
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:46,160
Or something that you understand

493
00:15:46,160 --> 00:15:47,800
And you see someone

494
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:50,040
Who is in that same kind of affinity

495
00:15:50,040 --> 00:15:51,680
That does the same things you do

496
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:53,160
Or maybe they're the same age as you are

497
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:54,560
Maybe they're someone you go to school with

498
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:56,000
Or someone you work with

499
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,840
But someone that you're connected with

500
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:59,000
In some way

501
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,920
And that's how God uses

502
00:16:00,920 --> 00:16:02,320
That connection is what God uses

503
00:16:02,320 --> 00:16:04,840
To bring that suffering in front of you

504
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:06,160
And to bring it close

505
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:08,080
And to allow you to see it

506
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:10,240
It could be a lot of different things

507
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:13,080
But just have your eyes open

508
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:16,920
And be aware of those things around you

509
00:16:16,920 --> 00:16:19,600
Again, no one should feel like

510
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:21,000
They need to fix every problem in the world

511
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:22,200
That's completely impossible

512
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,360
And if we think we can do that

513
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:25,520
Then our theology is way off

514
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:27,600
Only Jesus can do that

515
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:28,840
The only reason that

516
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:31,000
We're even supposed to be involved in all that

517
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:33,320
Is because we're supposed to be

518
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:34,200
The body of Christ

519
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:36,120
We're supposed to respond in love

520
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:36,680
And to serve

521
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:37,840
So it's not about us

522
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:39,400
It's not about me trying to

523
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:41,360
Be some superhero out there

524
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:42,280
Saving everyone

525
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:44,120
It's not that at all

526
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:45,880
But it is about Jesus

527
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:47,240
And his love for the lost

528
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:48,360
And his love for our world

529
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:49,520
And his love for the broken

530
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:50,600
And his love for the hurting

531
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:52,400
And his love for the oppressed

532
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:55,400
And because of his love for our world

533
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:57,880
He has told us as his people

534
00:16:57,880 --> 00:17:00,080
That he wants us to respond

535
00:17:00,080 --> 00:17:02,000
And to love and serve

536
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:04,360
And so we should be looking for those ways

537
00:17:04,360 --> 00:17:07,560
That Jesus brings that suffering

538
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:08,560
Into our lives

539
00:17:08,560 --> 00:17:10,440
And not just ignore it

540
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:11,640
Not just pass it by

541
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:12,720
But allow it to interrupt

542
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:13,640
The rhythms of our life

543
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:15,080
So that we can respond

544
00:17:15,080 --> 00:17:16,600
And become involved

545
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:18,120
And sometimes there's even suffering

546
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:19,480
Outside of your proximity

547
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:20,120
It's not something

548
00:17:20,120 --> 00:17:21,680
You would normally notice

549
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:23,440
That God brings before you

550
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:26,200
And be open to that as well

551
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:28,680
The type of ministry I do now

552
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:29,840
The neighborhood I live in

553
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:31,400
And raise my family in

554
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:33,000
Is a place that is very different

555
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,320
From where I grew up

556
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:35,720
I didn't grow up in the state

557
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:37,600
I didn't grow up in Chicago

558
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:39,680
But God brought me here

559
00:17:39,680 --> 00:17:42,560
In response to needs that were here

560
00:17:42,560 --> 00:17:43,800
That God cared about

561
00:17:43,800 --> 00:17:45,240
It's not about me

562
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:47,480
God cared about the needs that were here

563
00:17:47,480 --> 00:17:49,360
And so he brought me here

564
00:17:49,360 --> 00:17:50,720
To respond to him

565
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:51,600
And to obey him

566
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:52,920
And to love others

567
00:17:52,920 --> 00:17:54,800
That was outside my proximity

568
00:17:54,800 --> 00:17:56,240
But God brought it before me

569
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:57,400
And God might do that for you

570
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:59,360
God might bring something before you

571
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:01,040
